OL,3,CWhat can we all do to protect our
OL,4,Cmoney and plan for the future?
OL,6,F"Economic abuse is a dangerous form of
OL,7,Fcoercive control, which is the control
OL,8,Fof money and the things that money can
OL,9,Fbuy, and it really is at national
OL,10,Femergency levels now. We've got 1 in 7
OL,11,Fwomen experiencing it, that's 4.1
OL,12,Fmillion women across the UK. Living
OL,13,Fwith economic abuse. It's controlling
OL,14,Faccess to cash, their bank accounts,
OL,15,Frunning up debts in their name,
OL,16,Fdestroying their credit rating,
OL,17,Fdestroying their possessions,
OL,18,Fpreventing them from getting a job or
OL,19,Fholding on to a job. It's a very wide
OL,20,Franging form of abuse and causes
OL,21,Fintense harm".
